<p>The importance of expressing sympathy cannot be overstated.  A thoughtfully written condolence message, whether delivered in person, through a card, or digitally, can provide solace and comfort to someone grappling with loss.  Choosing the right words, while challenging, can make a real difference in helping someone navigate their grief. Remembering appropriate etiquette – such as avoiding clichés or insensitive comments, and timing your message appropriately – ensures your message is received with the respect and understanding it deserves.</p>
    

